<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1032.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>See the Department’s July 2. Provided your colleagues receive similar
                                instructions the Department approves.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>